  "correct_citations": [
    "In addition, a thermal-relaxation time correction is accounted for in the equilibrium limits to simulate the presence of non-equilibrated HQ distributions [39], which imply a reduced phase space for quarkonium production and thus a smaller equilibrium limit [36,38].• Constraints from lattice QCD The quarkonium spectral functions in the thermodynamic T -matrix approach, from which the combination of in-medium quarkonium binding energies and HQ masses are taken, have been constrained by Euclidean correlation functions computed in lQCD [75], and cross-checked using the widths as employed in the rate equation [34].",
